<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,221,389]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">
Only one species is known in the genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Franklin" authorityName="Franklin" box="[625,925,221,245]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Aleurodothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciapennis">
<emphasis box="[625,642,221,245]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[658,798,221,245]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">fasciapennis</emphasis>
(Franklin)
</taxonomicName>
. This is an obligate predator of scale insects (
<bibRefCitation author="Palmer" box="[158,424,257,281]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" refString="Palmer, JM. &amp; Mound, L. A. (1990) Thysanoptera. In: Rosen D. (Ed.), The armoured scale insects, their biology, natural enemies and control. Amsterdam (The Netherlands), Elsevier. pp. 67 - 75." type="book chapter" year="1990">
Palmer &amp; Mound 
<number box="[364,424,257,281]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" value="1990.0">1990</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and is recorded from many plants throughout the tropics and subtropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Okajima" box="[1258,1424,257,281]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" refString="Okajima, S. (2006) The Suborder Tubulifera (Thysanoptera). The Insects of Japan, 2, 1 - 720. The Entomological Society of Japan, Touka Shobo Co. Ltd., Fukuoka." type="journal article" year="2006">
Okajima 
<number box="[1363,1424,257,281]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The species is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[477,522,294,317]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="281">Iran</collectingCountry>
on the basis of one male collected on grape (
<bibRefCitation author="Mirab-balou" box="[1027,1331,293,317]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" refString="Mirab-balou, M. &amp; Chen, X. X. (2012) Aleurodothrips fasciapennis Franklin: A newly recorded genus and species for Iran (Thysanoptera: Phlaeothripidae). Munis Entomology &amp; Zoology, 7, 334 - 338." type="journal article" year="2012">
Mirab-balou &amp; Chen 
<number box="[1270,1331,293,317]" pageId="2" pageNumber="281" value="2012.0">2012</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
